    <text id="R14391463T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>In this October, 1864, dispatch, Union Assistant Adjutant John Schultze writes
                    from Chambersburg to Captian J. C. Hullinger with orders for his cavalry to
                    arrest draft evaders.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    HDQRS. DEPARTMENT OF THE SUSQUEHANNA,
                    <name type="recipient">Capt. J. C. HULLINGER,<lb/> Company D, 21st Regt.
                        Pennsylvania Cavalry, Pottsvile, Pa.:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-10-24">October 24, 1864.</date>
                        <name type="place">Chambersburg, Pa.,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>CAPT.:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>The commanding general directs that you proceed with your company, without delay,
                    to Stroudsburg, Pa., and report to Capt. Samuel Yohe, provost-marshal Eleventh
                    District, Easton, Pa., for orders. It is reported that the are over 1,500
                    drafted men in that district who have not reported. You are directed to arrest
                    them, or make it too uncomfortable for them to stay in that region. Those of
                    your command without horses will be left at Pottsville, under command of the
                    second lieutenant, who will use every exertion, after the inspection by Col.
                    Thomas S. Mather, to have the men mounted, and report to you with them for duty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am, captain, very respectfully, your obedient servant,</salute>
                    <signed>JNO. S. SCHULTZE,<lb/> Assistant Adjutant-Gen.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
